==English==

===Etymology===
From [[French]] ''[[taciturne]]'' or [[Latin]] ''[[taciturnus]]'', from ''[[tacitus]]'', [[silent]] (see [[tacit]]).

===Adjective===
'''taciturn'''
# Habitually [[untalkative]], silent
#:'' '''[[Guillaume le Taciturne]]''' is the French form of "William of Orange", [[w:William I of Orange]], best known as '''''[[w:William the Silent]].'''''

